HEADWORD: Anethum
<hw>Anethum</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a genus of plants of the parsley
family having aromatic seeds and finely divided leaves, including the
dill <spn>Anethum graveolens</spn>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> genus <gen>Anethum</gen>.</syn>⟦br⟧
